category.Name: category
category.Description: If this is set to “handoff”, the search returns only handoff records. If this is not set, handoff records are returned along with other kinds of DocumentReference instances that the client has scope to access, such as clinical notes, if the search parameters are valid for them.

encounter.Name: encounter
encounter.Description: FHIR Encounter ID. If provided, the search returns all matching handoff records for this encounter.
encounter.Optional: At least one of the following must be specified: encounter, patient, or subject

patient.Name: patient
patient.Description: FHIR Patient ID. If provided, the search returns all matching handoff records for this patient.
patient.Optional: At least one of the following must be specified: encounter, patient, or subject

subject.Name: subject
subject.Description: FHIR Patient ID. If provided, the search returns all matching handoff records for this patient.
subject.Optional: At least one of the following must be specified: encounter, patient, or subject

Bundle.Name: Bundle
Bundle.Description: Resource bundle. For more information, refer to the FHIR specification.

DocumentReference.Name: DocumentReference
DocumentReference.Description: An instance of the R4 DocumentReference resource.

author.Name: author
author.Description: The user who saved this edit to handoff.

category.Name: category
category.Description: Always coded as “handoff” in Epic’s “documentreference-category” coding system.

attachment.Name: attachment
attachment.Description: Absolute reference to Binary FHIR resource in Content.attachment.content

contentType.Name: contentType
contentType.Description: Always “text/html”. The Binary resource converts RTF and plain text to HTML.

url.Name: url
url.Description: Points to the Binary resource that represents this handoff record’s text.

encounter.Name: encounter
encounter.Description: The encounter that this handoff record is for

date.Name: date
date.Description: The instant at which handoff was updated on this contact.

handoff-purpose.Name: extension
handoff-purpose.Description: The purpose for which this record was created.

handoff-service.Name: extension
handoff-service.Description: The service for which this record was created.

status.Name: status
status.Description: “current” if this is the most recent SOD contact, or “superseded” for previous contacts.

subject.Name: subject
subject.Description: The patient with whom this handoff record is associated.
